Law enforcement officers came under attack while disconnecting illegal electricity connections in the Strandfontein &amp; Mitchells Plain area. CAPE TOWN - City of Cape Town law enforcement officers came under attack while disconnecting illegal electricity connections in the Strandfontein and Mitchells Plain area.Western Cape police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana says South African Police Service (SAPS) members were called in when the crowd started throwing stones. We re investigating a case of public violence after an incident which occurred on Tuesday afternoon. No arrests have been made. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)